<title>GERMANY: Buba official sees stability pact's importance.</title>
<headline>Buba official sees stability pact's importance.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>A stability pact, ensuring long-term fiscal austerity, needs to be a key pillar for Europe's currency union to be a success, a senior Bundesbank official said on Friday.</p>
<p>In excerpts from a speech prepared for delivery to public service officials, Bundesbank council member Franz-Christoph Zeitler again underscored the need for measures to ensure ongoing stability after the currency union is launched.</p>
<p>&quot;A stability pact needs to be a key and supporting pillar of the European currency union's architecture,&quot; Zeitler, also president of the state central bank in Bavaria, said.</p>
<p>--Svea Herbst-Bayliss, Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
